# GoModel local patch: drop Responses hosted/server tools before Chat translation.
#
# Context:
# - Codex CLI uses OpenAI Responses wire format and may send hosted tool
#   advertisements such as `web_search_preview`, `file_search`, and `container`.
# - GoModel's Responses-to-Chat bridge previously forwarded those tool entries
#   to Chat Completions providers.
# - Non-OpenAI providers such as Anthropic only accept ordinary function tools
#   in this path, so they returned `unsupported tool type` before a request could
#   complete.
#
# Fix:
# - Keep ordinary `type: function` tools.
# - Drop non-function Responses hosted/server tools when adapting to Chat.
# - If all tools are dropped, omit the Chat `tools` field.
#
# Generated from /home/xieby1/Codes/GoModel local diff against pinned GoModel
# v0.1.33 source revision 05775df604545ffb06c40509defc6cd16d26e6f6.
